            <ArticleTitle>Large-scale uniform optical focus array generation with a phase spatial light modulator.</ArticleTitle>
            <Pagination>
                <MedlinePgn>3178-3181</MedlinePgn>
            </Pagination>
            <ELocationID EIdType="doi" ValidYN="Y">10.1364/OL.44.003178</ELocationID>
            <Abstract>
                <AbstractText>In this Letter, to the best of our knowledge, we report a new method to generate uniform large-scale optical focus arrays (LOFAs). By identifying and removing undesired phase rotation in the iterative Fourier transform algorithm (IFTA), our approach rapidly produces computer-generated holograms of highly uniform LOFAs. The new algorithm also shows a faster compensation of system-induced LOFA intensity inhomogeneity than the conventional IFTA. After only three adaptive correction steps, we demonstrate LOFAs consisting of O(10<sup>3</sup>) optical foci with an intensity uniformity greater than 98%.</AbstractText>
            </Abstract>
